body:
The following rewritten from UVM tests/05components/50in_order/20int gives a false Verilation error:

```
%Error: t/t_0.v:16:43: Reference to 'T' type would form a recursive definition
   16 |       type comp_type = uvm_built_in_comp#(T)
      |                                           ^
```

```
module t;
  class uvm_built_in_comp #(
      type T = int
  );
  endclass

  class uvm_in_order_comparator #(
      type T = int,
      type comp_type = uvm_built_in_comp#(T)
  );
  endclass

  class uvm_in_order_built_in_comparator #(
      type T = int
  ) extends uvm_in_order_comparator #(T);
  endclass

  initial begin
    uvm_in_order_built_in_comparator #(int) sb;
    $finish;
  end
endmodule
```

I'll get back to this eventually, but anyone else that wants to investigate is very welcome to, thanks.

